<paragraph blockId="24.[136,1452,158,1373]" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,442,986,1012]" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[442,698,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">
— 
<taxonomicName box="[472,698,986,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">Bertolonia reginatoi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity box="[886,994,986,1015]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.898" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" unit="km" value="1898.0">1,898 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity box="[1160,1270,986,1015]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.069" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" unit="km" value="2069.0">2,069 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Endangered” (EN), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[650,802,1022,1048]" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found in the “Reserva Particular do Patrimônio Natural Serra Bonita”, and “Estação Ecológica Estadual de Wenceslau Guimarães”.
</paragraph>
