<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="177" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[136,1452,158,1373]" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1094,1120]" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,528,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">
<emphasis box="[294,528,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Bertolonia reginatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[715,783,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1306,1094,1121]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Fig. 13d</figureCitation>
), on shaded and moist slopes. Collected with flowers from December to February and June, and with fruits in February, May, September, and December. 
<taxonomicName box="[445,675,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">
<emphasis box="[445,675,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Bertolonia reginatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the long petioles (
<quantity box="[1076,1196,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="1.55" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" unit="cm" value="10.25" valueMax="15.5" valueMin="5.0">5–15.5 cm</quantity>
long), ovate to widely ovate leaf blades with a cordate base, margins densely ciliate, flowers with pink and apiculate petals, anthers with an undulate surface, and dehiscing through an introrse pore. 
<taxonomicName box="[770,998,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">
<emphasis box="[770,998,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Bertolonia reginatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<emphasis box="[1139,1255,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityYear="1990" box="[1139,1251,1239,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carmoi">B. carmoi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
however, the leaf margin in 
<taxonomicName box="[252,385,1275,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">
<emphasis box="[252,385,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">B. reginatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is brownish, which seems to be related to the dense trichomes found there. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[136,309,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
B. 
<emphasis box="[169,309,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[309,313,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">,</emphasis>
with populations at Wenceslau Guimarães occurring sympatrically. For more details, see notes under 
<taxonomicName box="[136,304,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis box="[136,304,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">B. hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[340,548,1346,1373]" pageId="24" pageNumber="177" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis box="[411,460,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="177">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[602,686,1346,1372]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." pageId="24" pageNumber="177">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
